WEBVTT

1
00:00:16.147 --> 00:00:19.107
The characters depicted in this film
are entirely fictitious.


2
00:00:19.307 --> 00:00:22.427
Any similarity to actual persons,
living or dead,


3
00:00:22.627 --> 00:00:26.747
is purely coincidental.

4
00:00:33.066 --> 00:00:35.786
THE PHANTOM OF LlBERTY

5
00:00:38.826 --> 00:00:41.826
"The action begins in Toledo, in 1808,

6
00:00:42.026 --> 00:00:45.825
during the city's occupation
by Napoleon's army.


7
00:00:46.025 --> 00:00:49.025
lt is inspired by a tale
by Gustavo A. Becquer,


8
00:00:49.225 --> 00:00:51.145
the Spanish romantic poet.''

9
00:02:08.859 --> 00:02:11.099
Prisoners against the wall!

10
00:02:15.778 --> 00:02:18.418
First row, take your positions!

11
00:02:20.138 --> 00:02:22.018
Ready, aim -

12
00:02:22.418 --> 00:02:24.058
Down with liberty!

13
00:02:24.258 --> 00:02:26.138
Death to the French!

14
00:02:27.098 --> 00:02:28.338
Fire!

15
00:03:13.974 --> 00:03:15.094
l'm hungry.

16
00:04:10.290 --> 00:04:13.810
Despite his wound,
and bent on revenge against the knight,


17
00:04:14.130 --> 00:04:16.929
the captain wagered his fellow officers

18
00:04:17.129 --> 00:04:21.849
that he could bring Dona Elvira's
mortal remains to his bed.


19
00:04:22.209 --> 00:04:24.809
Nothing could deter him from his intent,

20
00:04:25.049 --> 00:04:28.888
and one night
he carried out his macabre plan.


21
00:04:42.847 --> 00:04:45.047
The mysterious hand of death

22
00:04:45.447 --> 00:04:47.687
had spared her face,

23
00:04:47.887 --> 00:04:52.207
which had remained
as fresh and delicate as a rose.


24
00:04:53.007 --> 00:04:55.086
They found her
beneath her tombstone


25
00:04:55.286 --> 00:04:58.006
amid her repugnant paraphernal -

26
00:04:58.166 --> 00:04:59.526
What's that?

27
00:04:59.726 --> 00:05:03.086
"Paraphernalia.''
ls that a sweet-smelling herb?


28
00:05:03.966 --> 00:05:06.206
ls it a rosary?
- Not that either.


29
00:05:06.446 --> 00:05:09.965
lt's a legal term for the personal
property of a married woman.


30
00:05:11.405 --> 00:05:15.485
But in English, the word " paraphernalia''
has a much broader meaning.


31
00:05:16.565 --> 00:05:20.525
lt refers to any accoutrements,
belongings, personal items,


32
00:05:21.005 --> 00:05:22.804
even fishing gear

33
00:05:22.964 --> 00:05:24.684
or a sewing kit.

34
00:05:24.924 --> 00:05:27.764
- Where were you?
- We went biking over the bridge.


35
00:05:27.964 --> 00:05:29.124
We're going to the slide.

36
00:05:29.324 --> 00:05:31.724
We're going soon.
We'll come get you.


37
00:06:10.641 --> 00:06:12.441
You slid down so nicely.

38
00:06:13.161 --> 00:06:15.520
l think l know you.
What's your name?


39
00:06:15.760 --> 00:06:16.520
Veronique.

40
00:06:16.720 --> 00:06:18.160
- And you?
- Valerie.


41
00:06:18.360 --> 00:06:20.120
Yes, of course.

42
00:06:20.920 --> 00:06:22.960
Since you two are so nice,

43
00:06:23.280 --> 00:06:25.680
l'm going to give you a charming gift.

44
00:06:26.160 --> 00:06:28.519
Come with me -
- Our bikes are over there.


45
00:06:30.239 --> 00:06:31.359
Let's go.

46
00:06:45.078 --> 00:06:46.438
And now,

47
00:06:46.638 --> 00:06:50.158
l'm going to show you
some very pretty pictures.


48
00:06:51.598 --> 00:06:53.838
But you mustn't
show them to anyone.


49
00:06:55.117 --> 00:06:56.917
lf you want them,
you have to promise.


50
00:07:03.037 --> 00:07:04.437
Just look.

51
00:07:13.676 --> 00:07:15.076
They're for you.

52
00:07:15.436 --> 00:07:17.436
Show them to your friends.

53
00:07:17.756 --> 00:07:19.396
But no grown-ups.

54
00:07:19.676 --> 00:07:21.315
You'll remember that?

55
00:07:40.074 --> 00:07:41.914
l'm sick of symmetry.

56
00:07:54.673 --> 00:07:56.073
Henri.

57
00:07:56.313 --> 00:07:57.793
Back already?

58
00:07:57.993 --> 00:08:00.393
What do you mean?
l never went out.


59
00:08:01.752 --> 00:08:03.112
Don't you feel well?

60
00:08:04.112 --> 00:08:07.152
l don't know what's wrong.
l'm on edge, tired.


61
00:08:11.792 --> 00:08:13.032
lt's true.

62
00:08:13.232 --> 00:08:15.351
l've noticed it myself lately.

63
00:08:16.391 --> 00:08:18.751
Since Veronique's
on vacation this week,


64
00:08:18.951 --> 00:08:20.751
let's go down to the seashore.

65
00:08:20.951 --> 00:08:23.871
Why the sea?
The sea's no longer the sea.


66
00:08:26.951 --> 00:08:28.310
Hello, Mommy.

67
00:08:30.150 --> 00:08:31.750
Look what someone gave me.

68
00:08:32.910 --> 00:08:36.910
l passed you in the street yesterday
and you didn't even recognize me.


69
00:08:37.110 --> 00:08:39.150
l haven't been sleeping well lately.

70
00:08:39.470 --> 00:08:42.669
l haven't mentioned it,
but sometimes l lie awake all night.


71
00:08:42.989 --> 00:08:45.709
You should get a checkup,
just to be sure.


72
00:08:46.149 --> 00:08:49.789
Don't say " checkup. ''
There's a proper French term for it:


73
00:08:50.189 --> 00:08:51.149
general examination.

74
00:08:51.549 --> 00:08:54.388
lt's too long.
"General examination.''


75
00:08:54.628 --> 00:08:56.148
Checkup is much quicker.

76
00:08:56.348 --> 00:08:57.908
What's the hurry?

77
00:09:02.348 --> 00:09:03.268
Francoise!

78
00:09:09.867 --> 00:09:11.107
Come here.

79
00:09:12.907 --> 00:09:16.467
Where did you get these?
- A nice man gave them to me.


80
00:09:16.787 --> 00:09:19.147
So, you let her talk to strangers?

81
00:09:19.347 --> 00:09:22.266
l didn't see anything.
l didn't know.


82
00:09:22.506 --> 00:09:25.466
The man seemed very nice.
He even offered us candy.


83
00:09:26.306 --> 00:09:28.186
l've warned you before.

84
00:09:28.586 --> 00:09:31.866
lf you ever accept anything
from a stranger again,


85
00:09:32.066 --> 00:09:33.546
watch out!

86
00:09:33.746 --> 00:09:35.585
Time for her snack.
- Yes, madam.


87
00:09:44.985 --> 00:09:46.225
This is disgraceful!

88
00:09:46.465 --> 00:09:47.664
Let me see.

89
00:09:50.624 --> 00:09:51.864
Can you imagine!

90
00:09:52.064 --> 00:09:53.984
Disgusting, but what can you do?

91
00:09:54.184 --> 00:09:55.824
l'm at my wits' end.

92
00:09:56.024 --> 00:09:58.384
l can't always keep an eye on her.

93
00:09:59.064 --> 00:10:00.144
Look at this.

94
00:10:01.503 --> 00:10:03.663
Remember? lt was in Milan.

95
00:10:04.023 --> 00:10:05.663
At your parents' home.

96
00:10:06.863 --> 00:10:08.983
We were too young.

97
00:10:09.183 --> 00:10:10.823
But it was magnificent!

98
00:10:11.263 --> 00:10:12.863
And you didn't want to -

99
00:10:14.622 --> 00:10:16.302
Veronique might hear us.

100
00:10:28.861 --> 00:10:30.461
lncredible.

101
00:10:32.501 --> 00:10:33.901
Revolting.

102
00:10:36.701 --> 00:10:39.461
- Sickening!
- What can you expect nowadays?


103
00:10:40.660 --> 00:10:42.260
This one could pass.

104
00:10:46.020 --> 00:10:47.540
This one is indecent.

105
00:10:49.860 --> 00:10:52.340
That may be okay for old fogies,
but not for me.


106
00:10:59.579 --> 00:11:00.819
No, not this!

107
00:11:01.019 --> 00:11:02.899
- Let me see.
- What for?


108
00:11:03.099 --> 00:11:04.259
Why not?

109
00:11:04.499 --> 00:11:06.059
Let me see it.

110
00:11:12.898 --> 00:11:13.978
You're right.

111
00:11:14.258 --> 00:11:16.098
This is going too far.

112
00:11:19.498 --> 00:11:20.817
Call the maid.

113
00:11:25.777 --> 00:11:26.977
Francoise.

114
00:11:31.857 --> 00:11:34.896
l'm going to skip dinner tonight
and turn in early.


115
00:11:35.096 --> 00:11:37.616
You should see a doctor. l insist.

116
00:11:39.696 --> 00:11:42.376
- Here, you can keep them.
- Thanks, Daddy.


117
00:11:42.576 --> 00:11:44.536
May l trade them
for some spider pictures?


118
00:11:44.736 --> 00:11:46.216
lf you like.

119
00:11:49.015 --> 00:11:50.375
Madam called?

120
00:11:50.575 --> 00:11:53.735
After today's incident,
it's best you leave us.


121
00:11:53.935 --> 00:11:56.575
But l had nothing to do with it.
l didn't know -


122
00:11:56.775 --> 00:12:00.055
Settle things with my wife,
then get out.


123
00:12:00.374 --> 00:12:03.974
l'm sorry, but under the circumstances,
there's nothing l can do.


124
00:12:04.454 --> 00:12:07.054
Of course, you can stay the night.

125
00:12:07.254 --> 00:12:09.174
Let's work out what we owe you.

126
00:12:12.894 --> 00:12:16.413
- This one's a water spider.
- Very good, darling.


127
00:12:18.613 --> 00:12:21.733
l drew that one.
lt's a wolf spider.


128
00:12:21.933 --> 00:12:24.413
No, darling,
it's a trapdoor spider.


129
00:12:24.613 --> 00:12:27.212
A species you won't find in France,
sad to say.


130
00:13:27.688 --> 00:13:28.808
Helene.

131
00:14:53.441 --> 00:14:54.241
That's enough.

132
00:14:55.961 --> 00:14:57.521
That really is enough.

133
00:14:58.121 --> 00:14:59.841
l'm sorry, Mr. Foucauld,

134
00:15:00.361 --> 00:15:02.081
but this isn't my specialty.

135
00:15:02.441 --> 00:15:04.361
We're both wasting our time.

136
00:15:04.521 --> 00:15:06.121
But what should l do?

137
00:15:06.320 --> 00:15:08.800
Physically,
there's nothing wrong with you.


138
00:15:09.680 --> 00:15:12.560
lf you want to discuss your dreams,
see a psychoanalyst.


139
00:15:12.760 --> 00:15:16.560
He'll listen to you -
for months, years, if he has to.


140
00:15:16.760 --> 00:15:20.039
Doctor, it wasn't a dream.
l have the postman's letter.


141
00:15:20.319 --> 00:15:22.199
Look.

142
00:15:30.119 --> 00:15:31.879
- Doctor?
- What?


143
00:15:32.079 --> 00:15:33.678
May l see you a moment?

144
00:15:34.518 --> 00:15:35.598
Can't it wait?

145
00:15:35.798 --> 00:15:37.758
lt's rather urgent.

146
00:15:40.598 --> 00:15:41.758
Excuse me.

147
00:15:48.997 --> 00:15:50.517
My father is very sick.

148
00:15:52.837 --> 00:15:53.917
What's wrong with him?

149
00:15:54.237 --> 00:15:56.837
He's already had two attacks.
He's old.


150
00:15:57.077 --> 00:15:58.757
l'd like to go see him.

151
00:15:59.117 --> 00:16:01.476
We're very busy right now.

152
00:16:02.436 --> 00:16:04.156
Will you be away long?

153
00:16:04.356 --> 00:16:07.236
A couple of days.
l'll be back as soon as possible.


154
00:16:07.556 --> 00:16:10.716
- All right, then.
- Thank you, Doctor.


155
00:16:58.992 --> 00:17:01.312
Excuse me, did you see
any foxes on the road?


156
00:17:01.512 --> 00:17:03.512
Foxes? No.

157
00:17:04.032 --> 00:17:07.631
- No foxes crossing the road?
- l didn't see a thing.


158
00:17:08.351 --> 00:17:09.511
What'd l tell you!

159
00:17:09.711 --> 00:17:11.831
No foxes around here.
Never were!


160
00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:15.191
l had firsthand information, sir.
Maybe it's the storm.


161
00:17:15.511 --> 00:17:17.551
And we still have 30 miles to go.

162
00:17:17.751 --> 00:17:19.550
Enough time wasted! Let's go.

163
00:17:20.070 --> 00:17:22.830
Excuse me,
are you going toward Argenton?


164
00:17:24.790 --> 00:17:28.470
Be careful. There was a landslide
and the road may be out.


165
00:17:29.350 --> 00:17:30.870
Good-bye, ma'am.

166
00:17:35.709 --> 00:17:36.869
Let's go!

167
00:18:24.586 --> 00:18:26.425
May l use your phone?

168
00:18:26.625 --> 00:18:28.865
The line's down because of the floods.

169
00:18:29.065 --> 00:18:32.865
- What will l do now? Do you have a room?
- Of course. Front or back?


170
00:18:33.065 --> 00:18:34.825
lt doesn't matter.
l'm leaving early.


171
00:18:35.025 --> 00:18:36.145
Would you like supper?

172
00:18:36.345 --> 00:18:38.824
No, just some milk and fruit.

173
00:18:39.024 --> 00:18:41.944
l'll just be a minute.
Go and dry off.


174
00:18:53.623 --> 00:18:55.103
What hellish weather!

175
00:18:55.303 --> 00:18:57.263
lt seems the Argenton road is out.

176
00:18:57.783 --> 00:18:59.143
Have a seat, madam.

177
00:19:04.343 --> 00:19:06.342
We're stranded here too.

178
00:19:06.582 --> 00:19:09.742
- Are you from around here?
- My family is. And you?


179
00:19:10.262 --> 00:19:12.742
St. Joseph's Monastery.
You must know it.


180
00:19:12.942 --> 00:19:15.262
l've been there with my father.

181
00:19:15.462 --> 00:19:19.221
l'm going to see him. He's sick.
Who knows if l'll find him alive.


182
00:19:20.421 --> 00:19:21.581
What's wrong with him?

183
00:19:22.821 --> 00:19:24.141
l'm afraid for him.

184
00:19:24.821 --> 00:19:27.261
The heart.
The disease of our times.


185
00:19:27.581 --> 00:19:29.581
The bustle, the anxiety,

186
00:19:29.941 --> 00:19:31.061
the traveling.

187
00:19:31.621 --> 00:19:34.300
My father runs a small farm.
He never travels.


188
00:19:34.660 --> 00:19:37.460
He doesn't read the papers.
He doesn't have a phone.


189
00:19:39.260 --> 00:19:41.940
lf everybody prayed to St. Joseph

190
00:19:42.260 --> 00:19:45.659
and spent 30 minutes a day
in meditation,


191
00:19:46.379 --> 00:19:48.339
we'd all be perfectly relaxed.

192
00:19:48.539 --> 00:19:49.299
Surely.

193
00:19:52.539 --> 00:19:54.059
Whenever you're ready.

194
00:19:59.578 --> 00:20:01.098
This way.

195
00:20:26.856 --> 00:20:28.096
Excuse me, ma'am.

196
00:20:36.536 --> 00:20:38.415
Would you like an extra blanket?

197
00:20:38.615 --> 00:20:40.695
No, l sleep with the windows shut.

198
00:20:40.895 --> 00:20:42.535
ls there hot water?
- Of course.


199
00:20:42.735 --> 00:20:44.935
Shall l wake you?
- No need.


200
00:20:45.135 --> 00:20:46.855
Then good night, ma'am.

201
00:23:41.282 --> 00:23:42.122
Who is it?

202
00:23:42.682 --> 00:23:45.401
lt's Father Gabriel.
l'd like a word with you.


203
00:23:46.841 --> 00:23:48.161
Just a moment.

204
00:23:54.921 --> 00:23:57.081
Good evening, madam.
May l?


205
00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:02.680
Do you know what this is?
- Yes. lt's an image.


206
00:24:03.200 --> 00:24:05.240
A miraculous image of St. Joseph.

207
00:24:05.440 --> 00:24:07.920
lt can have surprising effects
on the sick.


208
00:24:08.120 --> 00:24:10.480
- Really?
- l'm thinking of your father.


209
00:24:10.840 --> 00:24:14.719
Faith can sometimes triumph
where science has failed.


210
00:24:15.839 --> 00:24:18.359
We just saw
the Marquise de la Pomarede.


211
00:24:18.559 --> 00:24:20.439
Yesterday she was near death.

212
00:24:20.639 --> 00:24:23.519
We brought her the image.

213
00:24:24.358 --> 00:24:25.918
We prayed.

214
00:24:26.878 --> 00:24:29.478
This morning
when we left the chateau -


215
00:24:29.678 --> 00:24:32.118
- She was cured?
- She felt a little better.


216
00:24:35.038 --> 00:24:36.558
You play cards, madam?

217
00:24:37.158 --> 00:24:39.157
Sometimes, when l'm alone.

218
00:24:39.677 --> 00:24:40.917
l play solitaire.

219
00:24:41.117 --> 00:24:42.997
So do l. lt's very relaxing.

220
00:24:43.717 --> 00:24:45.317
That must be the fathers.

221
00:24:57.356 --> 00:24:59.596
And now, with your permission,

222
00:25:00.276 --> 00:25:02.156
we shall pray for your father.

223
00:25:02.596 --> 00:25:05.795
l don't know how to thank you.
l'm deeply touched.


224
00:25:14.795 --> 00:25:16.355
Would you like a rosary?

225
00:25:16.635 --> 00:25:17.714
Yes, thank you.

226
00:25:29.754 --> 00:25:32.153
Let us meditate tonight
on the sorrowful mystery


227
00:25:32.313 --> 00:25:34.953
of Christ's agony
on the Mount of Olives.


228
00:25:35.153 --> 00:25:36.953
Our Father, who art in heaven...

229
00:25:52.432 --> 00:25:54.712
Hail Mary, full of grace...

230
00:25:57.911 --> 00:26:00.271
Holy Mary, Mother of God,
pray for us sinners


231
00:26:00.471 --> 00:26:02.751
now and at the hour of our death.
Amen.


232
00:26:13.430 --> 00:26:15.510
- l'm in.
- Raise you 10.


233
00:26:15.710 --> 00:26:18.670
- Pass.
- l'll see you and raise you a scapular.


234
00:26:24.469 --> 00:26:25.749
l open.

235
00:26:29.549 --> 00:26:31.149
- How many cards?
- Two.


236
00:26:36.589 --> 00:26:39.068
Virgins are 10
and sacred hearts are 25, right?


237
00:26:39.268 --> 00:26:41.148
Yes, and scapulars are 50.

238
00:26:41.948 --> 00:26:43.108
l open with a virgin.

239
00:26:47.828 --> 00:26:49.468
Full house, jacks over eights.

240
00:26:53.867 --> 00:26:56.947
Didn't you say your father
once lived in the colonies?


241
00:26:57.747 --> 00:27:00.267
No. He never left
these parts. Why?


242
00:27:00.467 --> 00:27:01.627
Oh, nothing.

243
00:27:01.827 --> 00:27:03.147
Place your bets.

244
00:27:05.906 --> 00:27:07.866
She was so mischievous.

245
00:27:08.186 --> 00:27:09.386
Who?

246
00:27:09.586 --> 00:27:13.906
A pious lady who used to visit us.
Her husband was in the army.


247
00:27:14.466 --> 00:27:16.586
- What about her?
- Nothing, nothing.


248
00:27:16.786 --> 00:27:17.985
Father Gabriel.

249
00:27:18.825 --> 00:27:21.025
l didn't say anything unusual.

250
00:27:25.025 --> 00:27:27.145
Those must be the late guests
l was expecting.


251
00:27:27.345 --> 00:27:29.425
lf you'll excuse me.

252
00:27:33.264 --> 00:27:35.224
Which is higher,
a flush or a straight?


253
00:27:35.424 --> 00:27:36.784
A flush.

254
00:27:38.104 --> 00:27:39.144
Then l raise you 10.

255
00:27:57.142 --> 00:27:59.462
- ls our room ready?
- Yes. lt's very nice.


256
00:28:00.142 --> 00:28:02.702
You have a view of the mountain.
Very quiet.


257
00:28:03.502 --> 00:28:07.102
lt's late, but if you want dinner,
a snack or a sandwich -


258
00:28:07.302 --> 00:28:09.982
No, thank you. The lady is tired.
We'll get some rest.


259
00:28:10.821 --> 00:28:12.661
Take their luggage up.

260
00:28:29.100 --> 00:28:31.340
What time would you like breakfast?

261
00:28:31.900 --> 00:28:33.420
We'll come down.

262
00:28:48.699 --> 00:28:51.458
Would madam like anything?
A bottle of mineral water?


263
00:28:51.658 --> 00:28:52.938
Nothing, thank you.

264
00:28:56.618 --> 00:28:57.978
Good night.

265
00:29:13.457 --> 00:29:14.977
Alea jacta est.

266
00:29:17.456 --> 00:29:18.776
What do you mean?

267
00:29:18.976 --> 00:29:20.176
That this is wonderful.

268
00:29:21.576 --> 00:29:23.576
Come sit next to me. Come on.

269
00:29:25.736 --> 00:29:28.096
- The things you make me do -
- Don't be nervous.


270
00:29:28.616 --> 00:29:30.575
You heard the man.
lt's very quiet here.


271
00:29:31.175 --> 00:29:32.935
- Too quiet.
- Sit down.


272
00:29:36.215 --> 00:29:37.495
Take off your glasses.

273
00:29:44.934 --> 00:29:47.774
What's wrong?
You seemed so happy about coming.


274
00:29:48.534 --> 00:29:51.534
- Why did l listen to you?
- How l've waited for this.


275
00:29:51.734 --> 00:29:54.494
Please, Francois, take me home.

276
00:29:55.174 --> 00:29:56.653
Why did you come then?

277
00:29:57.173 --> 00:29:59.013
Because l can't refuse you anything.

278
00:30:04.533 --> 00:30:06.093
For once we're alone,

279
00:30:06.413 --> 00:30:08.493
without my mother,
my brothers, my sisters.


280
00:30:09.572 --> 00:30:13.692
lt had become unbearable, having you
near me, always having to lie.


281
00:30:13.932 --> 00:30:15.532
For me as well, Francois.

282
00:30:16.252 --> 00:30:18.212
But how can we avoid lying?

283
00:30:23.851 --> 00:30:25.411
Sit down here.

284
00:30:29.611 --> 00:30:31.571
All my life, l've
felt you close to me.

285
00:30:32.411 --> 00:30:34.251
Your perfume, your presence.

286
00:30:37.010 --> 00:30:40.290
The times l held you on my lap
when you were a child.


287
00:30:41.370 --> 00:30:44.330
When l think of a woman,
it's always you l see.


288
00:30:45.090 --> 00:30:47.210
Of all my nephews,

289
00:30:47.450 --> 00:30:49.370
l've always loved you the best.

290
00:30:55.769 --> 00:30:57.369
Remember that Holy Thursday,

291
00:30:58.009 --> 00:31:00.449
sitting side by side
in the church's dim light?


292
00:31:01.809 --> 00:31:03.928
Your hand was resting on the pew.

293
00:31:04.728 --> 00:31:08.608
Gently, l put my hand on yours
and squeezed it.


294
00:31:09.248 --> 00:31:11.448
l felt your fingers close around mine.

295
00:31:12.568 --> 00:31:14.168
l didn't dare believe it.

296
00:31:14.848 --> 00:31:16.327
l waited for a moment.

297
00:31:16.687 --> 00:31:18.927
Then l looked at you.

298
00:31:19.727 --> 00:31:22.807
You looked at me
and leaned toward me,


299
00:31:23.927 --> 00:31:26.407
and we kissed for the first time.

300
00:31:27.327 --> 00:31:29.047
We couldn't help ourselves.

301
00:31:44.605 --> 00:31:46.325
l won't touch you.

302
00:31:46.685 --> 00:31:48.645
But there's one thing
l want more than anything.


303
00:31:48.845 --> 00:31:49.925
What?

304
00:31:50.325 --> 00:31:52.005
- To see you naked.
- lmpossible.


305
00:31:52.205 --> 00:31:55.125
- l won't leave here until l do.
- l couldn't.


306
00:31:55.365 --> 00:32:00.004
l've never been naked in front of a man.
No man has ever touched me.


307
00:32:01.204 --> 00:32:02.564
Take off your clothes.

308
00:32:03.484 --> 00:32:05.684
lf you refuse,
you know l'll stop at nothing.


309
00:32:08.004 --> 00:32:09.203
Shit!

310
00:32:23.442 --> 00:32:24.762
Take off your clothes.

311
00:32:25.762 --> 00:32:27.722
You promise you won't touch me?

312
00:32:29.442 --> 00:32:30.922
Lock the door.

313
00:32:37.241 --> 00:32:38.321
Turn around.

314
00:32:59.320 --> 00:33:01.040
lt's no good. l can't do it.

315
00:33:01.600 --> 00:33:03.719
- But you said -
- l said nothing!


316
00:33:05.719 --> 00:33:08.519
What's got into you? Stop it!

317
00:33:10.039 --> 00:33:12.119
You swear you won't touch me?

318
00:33:12.319 --> 00:33:13.719
l swear.

319
00:33:15.479 --> 00:33:16.718
Turn around.

320
00:33:29.877 --> 00:33:31.957
What must they be thinking at home?

321
00:33:33.917 --> 00:33:35.437
They'll be waiting for us.

322
00:33:40.517 --> 00:33:43.396
You know your mother.
She's so easily worried.


323
00:33:45.556 --> 00:33:47.836
They may think we had an accident.

324
00:33:48.436 --> 00:33:50.556
What with the phone lines down...

325
00:33:52.636 --> 00:33:55.076
Well, too bad. We'll see.

326
00:34:03.995 --> 00:34:05.275
Are you ready?

327
00:34:05.555 --> 00:34:07.715
You can turn around if you want.

328
00:34:14.234 --> 00:34:15.994
For pity's sake, Francois.

329
00:34:17.714 --> 00:34:18.954
Don't be frightened.

330
00:34:19.194 --> 00:34:20.394
Let me.

331
00:34:21.954 --> 00:34:23.193
You swore.

332
00:34:37.112 --> 00:34:38.472
One second.

333
00:34:51.711 --> 00:34:53.351
lt's better like this, isn't it?

334
00:34:57.871 --> 00:34:59.751
Let go of me or l'll scream!

335
00:35:00.511 --> 00:35:02.150
Help!

336
00:35:38.828 --> 00:35:40.188
l'll light your way.

337
00:35:43.627 --> 00:35:46.307
Just light a candle
and the power comes back.


338
00:35:46.507 --> 00:35:48.147
Going downstairs?
- To the bar.


339
00:35:48.347 --> 00:35:49.827
The bar's closed.

340
00:35:50.667 --> 00:35:53.907
Come to my room. We were
just about to open some port.


341
00:35:55.426 --> 00:35:57.866
Yes, come in. Just for a minute.
Please do.


342
00:36:06.986 --> 00:36:08.425
Do come in.

343
00:36:13.545 --> 00:36:16.505
My dear,
allow me to introduce Mr. -


344
00:36:16.705 --> 00:36:18.425
Francois de Richemont.

345
00:36:18.785 --> 00:36:20.865
- Miss Rosenblum.
- Pleased to meet you.


346
00:36:22.024 --> 00:36:23.224
The pleasure's mine.

347
00:36:23.464 --> 00:36:24.864
My name is Jean Bermans.

348
00:36:27.264 --> 00:36:28.544
Do sit down.

349
00:36:31.704 --> 00:36:33.464
Are you from Paris?

350
00:36:33.664 --> 00:36:34.983
Yes. Are you?

351
00:36:35.183 --> 00:36:39.183
No, l'm a hatter from Nimes.
Miss Rosenblum is my associate.


352
00:36:40.223 --> 00:36:41.743
Are you in business too?

353
00:36:41.943 --> 00:36:44.823
- No, l'm a student.
- What are you studying?


354
00:36:45.223 --> 00:36:46.663
l'm graduating high school.

355
00:36:46.863 --> 00:36:48.462
Lucky young fellow.

356
00:36:48.662 --> 00:36:51.422
l have fond memories
of my student days.


357
00:36:51.782 --> 00:36:55.142
lf only l could have gone to college.
But in Ostend, you know -


358
00:36:55.942 --> 00:36:57.062
Are you here alone?

359
00:36:57.262 --> 00:36:58.742
No, l'm with -

360
00:36:59.262 --> 00:37:00.782
my mother.

361
00:37:01.541 --> 00:37:03.621
Perhaps she'd care to join us.

362
00:37:03.941 --> 00:37:05.381
l don't think so.

363
00:37:05.541 --> 00:37:07.021
She's not feeling well.

364
00:37:08.261 --> 00:37:09.581
One moment.

365
00:37:14.021 --> 00:37:16.660
l'm sorry, but l heard voices.
l'm looking for matches.


366
00:37:16.860 --> 00:37:18.940
Come in.
Sit down for a minute.


367
00:37:19.140 --> 00:37:21.340
Yes, but...
l'm with four gentlemen.


368
00:37:22.500 --> 00:37:23.860
Four gentlemen?

369
00:37:24.180 --> 00:37:26.780
We might invite them in too.

370
00:37:26.980 --> 00:37:28.779
That would be lovely.

371
00:37:30.219 --> 00:37:32.139
Will you show me to your room?

372
00:37:32.339 --> 00:37:34.539
- Yes, but -
- Come.


373
00:37:35.139 --> 00:37:37.259
Which door?
- That one.


374
00:37:44.618 --> 00:37:46.698
She didn't tell me
the gentlemen were -


375
00:37:47.178 --> 00:37:49.058
But it's no problem.
On the contrary.


376
00:37:49.898 --> 00:37:51.258
Jean Bermans.

377
00:37:51.498 --> 00:37:56.057
Gentlemen, l'd be honored if you'd come
have some port in my room.


378
00:37:56.257 --> 00:37:57.217
ln your room?

379
00:37:57.417 --> 00:38:01.457
- That's very kind of you, but -
- l'd be so pleased.


380
00:38:01.657 --> 00:38:03.737
lt's late. We were going to bed.

381
00:38:03.937 --> 00:38:06.737
We must celebrate the chance
that brought us together.


382
00:38:06.937 --> 00:38:10.256
- Celebrate what?
- Chance. Come along.


383
00:38:10.536 --> 00:38:12.176
Come along, please.

384
00:38:17.936 --> 00:38:19.296
This way.

385
00:38:27.855 --> 00:38:29.895
After you.

386
00:38:35.614 --> 00:38:36.854
Please go in.

387
00:38:39.294 --> 00:38:40.894
You must be Dominicans?

388
00:38:41.094 --> 00:38:43.214
- No, Carmelites.
- That's a relief.


389
00:38:51.133 --> 00:38:53.293
My dear Edith,
isn't this a stroke of luck?


390
00:38:53.493 --> 00:38:56.693
This is Miss Rosenblum.
- Pleased to meet you.


391
00:38:56.893 --> 00:38:58.893
Edith, pour us some port, will you?

392
00:38:59.093 --> 00:39:01.452
Mr. de Richemont,
will you give me a hand?


393
00:39:01.932 --> 00:39:05.772
lt's a bit cramped in here, but no matter.
We love these little impromptus.


394
00:39:06.812 --> 00:39:11.412
We're going to have a charming time,
if you have no objections.


395
00:39:11.772 --> 00:39:13.132
Excuse me.

396
00:39:15.371 --> 00:39:18.491
Mr. Bermans,
haven't we met before?


397
00:39:18.691 --> 00:39:19.691
l don't think so.

398
00:39:19.931 --> 00:39:22.291
You never lived in the Congo?

399
00:39:22.491 --> 00:39:23.411
The Belgian Congo.

400
00:39:23.611 --> 00:39:26.491
- l've never been to Africa. Why?
- No reason.


401
00:39:27.051 --> 00:39:29.370
- The weather's improving.
- lt's about time.


402
00:39:29.570 --> 00:39:32.050
Personally, l love Africa.

403
00:39:44.489 --> 00:39:46.609
St. Christopher was never
any help to me.


404
00:39:46.809 --> 00:39:49.249
- Naturally, madam.
- Why's that?


405
00:39:49.449 --> 00:39:52.729
He's no longer a saint.
Nor are St. George and some others.


406
00:39:52.929 --> 00:39:56.528
The church has become very strict
about sainthood.


407
00:39:57.088 --> 00:39:59.488
But isn't that damaging to the faith?

408
00:39:59.688 --> 00:40:02.048
On the contrary. lt reinforces it.

409
00:40:02.248 --> 00:40:04.728
Sainthood isn't like some badge.

410
00:40:19.567 --> 00:40:22.686
You've no doubt heard of Savonarola?

411
00:40:22.886 --> 00:40:26.926
- Wasn't he a Dominican?
- lndeed, and an illustrious one.


412
00:40:27.126 --> 00:40:30.006
