a question of changing the laws.


516
00:51:26.796 --> 00:51:30.076
We also hear a lot about an evolution

517
00:51:30.356 --> 00:51:32.796
that is leading to changes in customs

518
00:51:32.996 --> 00:51:34.036
and morals.

519
00:51:59.154 --> 00:52:01.074
Hey, look at this.

520
00:52:07.433 --> 00:52:09.633
RED DAlLY
Workers Sound the Alarm!


521
00:52:11.353 --> 00:52:12.953
Attention!

522
00:52:19.112 --> 00:52:20.952
- Colonel.
- Go ahead.


523
00:52:24.952 --> 00:52:29.032
l was told the class
was a bit restless today. We'll see.


524
00:52:29.592 --> 00:52:30.552
Sit down.

525
00:52:39.071 --> 00:52:40.631
Carry on.

526
00:52:44.271 --> 00:52:47.510
There's a good deal of talk
about changing our morals.


527
00:52:48.390 --> 00:52:51.790
Some people are even calling
for a general upheaval.


528
00:52:53.030 --> 00:52:58.829
But the consequences of such
a disturbance could prove intolerable,


529
00:52:59.029 --> 00:53:00.589
even horrifying.

530
00:53:01.269 --> 00:53:03.829
l'll pick an example at random.

531
00:53:04.029 --> 00:53:06.629
My wife and l are invited
over to some friends...


532
00:53:23.668 --> 00:53:27.467
- We thought you'd never make it.
- You can't imagine the traffic.


533
00:53:27.667 --> 00:53:29.067
We nearly began without you.

534
00:53:29.267 --> 00:53:31.627
- You should have.
- You're not serious!


535
00:53:31.827 --> 00:53:33.227
Why, here's Sophie!

536
00:53:33.467 --> 00:53:35.347
Sweetheart, how are you?

537
00:53:36.347 --> 00:53:38.746
How you've grown!
Everything fine at school?


538
00:53:41.586 --> 00:53:43.226
You know Mrs. Calmette.

539
00:53:46.746 --> 00:53:49.666
lf you'll just follow me...

540
00:53:52.105 --> 00:53:53.265
Let's see.

541
00:53:53.465 --> 00:53:56.945
Mrs. Calmette, you sit there.

542
00:53:57.665 --> 00:53:59.265
Elizabeth, here.

543
00:53:59.465 --> 00:54:01.385
You, Professor, at my right.

544
00:54:01.665 --> 00:54:04.145
Charles, between Elizabeth
and Mrs. Calmette.


545
00:54:04.344 --> 00:54:06.624
And you, Sophie darling,

546
00:54:06.824 --> 00:54:08.424
sit on my left.

547
00:54:08.624 --> 00:54:10.224
Do sit down.

548
00:54:18.863 --> 00:54:21.903
We went to see Tristan and lsolde
the other day.


549
00:54:22.063 --> 00:54:23.543
- Was it good?
- Splendid.


550
00:54:23.743 --> 00:54:28.503
Carlotta lgellicci was heartrending.
What a voice! What presence!


551
00:54:28.863 --> 00:54:31.102
lt's a shame she's put on weight.

552
00:54:32.822 --> 00:54:34.542
Care for a cigarette?

553
00:54:34.862 --> 00:54:36.222
l'd love one, thanks.

554
00:54:37.502 --> 00:54:40.462
- How was your trip to Spain?
- lnteresting.


555
00:54:40.822 --> 00:54:42.222
But -
- But?


556
00:54:42.422 --> 00:54:43.862
We had to come home early.

557
00:54:44.062 --> 00:54:47.021
Madrid was filled with the stench of -

558
00:54:47.301 --> 00:54:48.541
pardon my language -

559
00:54:48.741 --> 00:54:50.261
food.

560
00:54:50.861 --> 00:54:53.021
lt was indecent.

561
00:54:53.221 --> 00:54:58.260
What will our planet be like in 20 years
with the current population explosion?


562
00:54:58.740 --> 00:55:00.140
lt makes you think.

563
00:55:00.460 --> 00:55:02.700
What are you referring to?

564
00:55:03.060 --> 00:55:06.860
Consider the quantity of toxic products
we dump into our rivers.


565
00:55:07.060 --> 00:55:09.260
lnsecticides, detergents,

566
00:55:09.460 --> 00:55:11.339
all the industrial residue.

567
00:55:12.539 --> 00:55:15.899
- Not to mention bodily wastes.
- Of course.


568
00:55:16.099 --> 00:55:19.899
There are almost
four billion people on earth.


569
00:55:20.139 --> 00:55:22.219
ln 20 years there'll be
seven billion of us.


570
00:55:22.419 --> 00:55:23.819
Seven billion!

571
00:55:25.138 --> 00:55:28.738
And how much bodily waste
do you think a person discharges daily?


572
00:55:30.658 --> 00:55:33.338
l don't know.
Half a pound, maybe?


573
00:55:33.538 --> 00:55:35.458
Much more!

574
00:55:35.658 --> 00:55:37.737
Urine is heavier than water.

575
00:55:37.937 --> 00:55:41.017
All told, l'd say
at least three pounds.


576
00:55:41.217 --> 00:55:43.337
Multiplied by four billion,

577
00:55:43.497 --> 00:55:45.337
that makes more than

578
00:55:45.537 --> 00:55:47.897
ln 20 years,
more than 22 billion pounds!


579
00:55:48.257 --> 00:55:51.016
- Ten million tons of excrement a day?
- Exactly.


580
00:55:51.176 --> 00:55:52.456
My word!

581
00:55:53.136 --> 00:55:55.576
That's really alarming!

582
00:55:57.896 --> 00:55:59.176
How many tons did you say?

583
00:55:59.936 --> 00:56:02.056
More than 10 million tons a day.

584
00:56:03.656 --> 00:56:06.055
And such waste is extremely toxic.

585
00:56:06.255 --> 00:56:09.855
lts damaging effect is increased
by the presence of chemicals.


586
00:56:10.335 --> 00:56:14.175
Just try peeing
into your fish tank every day


587
00:56:14.375 --> 00:56:15.695
and you'll understand.

588
00:56:18.054 --> 00:56:19.974
Mommy, l'm really hungry.

589
00:56:20.414 --> 00:56:23.014
Sophie, it's bad manners
to talk like that at the table!


590
00:56:26.614 --> 00:56:28.294
Excuse me a moment.

591
00:56:31.053 --> 00:56:32.613
Where's the dining room, please?

592
00:56:32.813 --> 00:56:34.853
Last door on the right.

593
00:57:27.649 --> 00:57:28.449
lt's occupied!

594
00:57:28.649 --> 00:57:30.209
Sorry!

595
00:57:38.008 --> 00:57:38.968
What is it?

596
00:57:39.168 --> 00:57:41.888
Colonel, we go on duty
at 1 1 :00 a.m.

597
00:57:43.128 --> 00:57:44.328
Go ahead then.

598
00:58:38.484 --> 00:58:40.364
Driver's license and registration.

599
00:58:47.003 --> 00:58:50.123
- Don't you know the speed limit?
- l was doing under 40.


600
00:58:50.323 --> 00:58:51.483
Really?

601
00:58:52.523 --> 00:58:54.043
And the seat belt is compulsory.

602
00:58:54.243 --> 00:58:56.363
l know. l wasn't thinking.

603
00:59:06.602 --> 00:59:08.482
Have you seen your tires?

604
00:59:10.401 --> 00:59:12.881
You're not only endangering
your own life


605
00:59:13.281 --> 00:59:15.081
but that of other drivers.

606
00:59:15.321 --> 00:59:17.601
l have a doctor's appointment in Paris.

607
00:59:17.801 --> 00:59:19.561
Are you kidding me?

608
00:59:23.121 --> 00:59:25.480
Consider yourself lucky
l don't impound your car.


609
00:59:37.999 --> 00:59:40.679
Richard, how are you feeling,
old man?


610
00:59:40.879 --> 00:59:42.319
No better, no worse.

611
00:59:42.559 --> 00:59:45.879
- And your wife and little girl?
- Fine, thank you.


612
00:59:46.199 --> 00:59:48.879
You must come over
for dinner some evening.


613
00:59:49.119 --> 00:59:50.678
We'd like that.

614
00:59:59.958 --> 01:00:01.118
Sit down.

615
01:00:03.077 --> 01:00:04.917
Did you bring the test results?

616
01:00:06.877 --> 01:00:08.117
Let's have a look.

617
01:00:11.237 --> 01:00:12.757
Glucose: 130.

618
01:00:12.957 --> 01:00:14.757
Cholesterol, fine.

619
01:00:15.117 --> 01:00:16.916
Uric acid... urea...

620
01:00:17.276 --> 01:00:18.476
good.

621
01:00:26.396 --> 01:00:27.556
Very good.

622
01:00:28.596 --> 01:00:32.035
Your results are better than mine.
Now for the electrocardiogram.


623
01:00:38.995 --> 01:00:40.795
Normal.

624
01:00:41.395 --> 01:00:43.154
You smoke a lot?
- A pack a day.


625
01:00:43.354 --> 01:00:44.754
Too much.

626
01:00:46.034 --> 01:00:47.754
And you lead a hectic life.

627
01:00:47.954 --> 01:00:52.474
Keep it up and in three or four years
you'll end up in a wheelchair.


628
01:00:53.514 --> 01:00:55.034
Let's look at the X rays.

629
01:01:08.113 --> 01:01:10.552
This area here is clear, see?

630
01:01:10.832 --> 01:01:12.632
There's a small spot here.

631
01:01:12.992 --> 01:01:15.632
We could take another X ray
to be sure.


632
01:01:16.032 --> 01:01:17.872
And those white spots?

633
01:01:18.072 --> 01:01:19.712
Oh, nothing.

634
01:01:20.712 --> 01:01:25.591
Catherine met your wife the other day.
So you're not going south this summer?


635
01:01:25.791 --> 01:01:28.471
lf l'm not feeling well,
we'll stay in Paris.


636
01:01:31.671 --> 01:01:33.791
All right. Well?

637
01:01:35.951 --> 01:01:37.030
One thing.

638
01:01:37.230 --> 01:01:40.110
l'd like to make a small incision.

639
01:01:40.590 --> 01:01:42.270
Sheer medical curiosity.

640
01:01:42.470 --> 01:01:44.590
- Big?
- This long.


641
01:01:46.670 --> 01:01:47.790
ls it an operation?

642
01:01:47.990 --> 01:01:49.509
Just to see.

643
01:01:50.709 --> 01:01:51.389
When?

644
01:01:51.589 --> 01:01:53.709
Whenever you want.
When you have time.


645
01:01:56.029 --> 01:01:57.549
ls tomorrow okay with you?

646
01:01:59.589 --> 01:02:01.309
Tomorrow? ls it that urgent?

647
01:02:01.549 --> 01:02:04.468
lt's always best to do these things
as soon as possible.


648
01:02:05.268 --> 01:02:06.068
What's wrong?

649
01:02:06.468 --> 01:02:07.948
lt's up to you,

650
01:02:08.148 --> 01:02:11.188
but personally,
l'd like to have a look.


651
01:02:18.147 --> 01:02:19.787
Look, Pierre,

652
01:02:20.067 --> 01:02:21.667
l'm not a child anymore.

653
01:02:21.987 --> 01:02:24.747
lf it's something serious,
you can tell me.


654
01:02:25.027 --> 01:02:26.667
l like patients like you.

655
01:02:28.267 --> 01:02:29.906
You have a neoplasm.

656
01:02:33.866 --> 01:02:35.306
l see.

657
01:02:39.346 --> 01:02:40.386
What's that?

658
01:02:40.586 --> 01:02:42.785
A growth of new tissue.

659
01:02:43.145 --> 01:02:45.185
Or, if you prefer, cancer.

660
01:02:46.025 --> 01:02:47.225
What?

661
01:02:47.825 --> 01:02:49.825
You have cancer of the liver.

662
01:02:52.825 --> 01:02:54.505
Cancer, me?

663
01:02:54.705 --> 01:02:56.824
At a fairly advanced stage.

664
01:03:07.864 --> 01:03:09.703
But nowadays, you know,

665
01:03:10.103 --> 01:03:11.463
these things...

666
01:03:12.263 --> 01:03:13.623
Cigarette?

667
01:04:11.819 --> 01:04:13.779
What did Dr. Pasolini say?

668
01:04:14.339 --> 01:04:15.419
lt's nothing.

669
01:04:15.618 --> 01:04:16.858
Oh, good.

670
01:04:17.098 --> 01:04:18.378
That's a relief.

671
01:04:19.698 --> 01:04:21.418
l was a bit worried, you know.

672
01:04:24.258 --> 01:04:26.978
Did he start you on treatment?
- No, nothing.


673
01:04:28.578 --> 01:04:30.057
lsn't Aliette here?

674
01:04:30.257 --> 01:04:32.217
She's at school now.

675
01:04:40.697 --> 01:04:42.256
Yes, speaking.

676
01:04:43.736 --> 01:04:45.336
What did you say?

677
01:04:47.336 --> 01:04:49.056
When? How?

678
01:04:49.856 --> 01:04:51.296
That's impossible.

679
01:04:53.096 --> 01:04:54.776
We'll be right over.

680
01:04:55.535 --> 01:04:57.855
- What is it?
- Aliette's disappeared.


681
01:04:58.055 --> 01:05:00.295
- What?
- She's disappeared from school.


682
01:05:00.495 --> 01:05:03.615
There must be an explanation.
Did the nanny take her?


683
01:05:04.135 --> 01:05:06.735
Yes. She just got back.
She didn't say a thing.


684
01:05:14.054 --> 01:05:15.574
Brigitte!

685
01:05:23.213 --> 01:05:25.613
Exactly what happened?

686
01:05:25.813 --> 01:05:27.973
l don't know.
We don't understand it.


687
01:05:28.253 --> 01:05:31.293
- You're sure she's disappeared?
- l don't know.


688
01:05:31.773 --> 01:05:33.413
What makes it so odd

689
01:05:33.813 --> 01:05:38.132
is that she and the others
were under constant supervision.


690
01:05:38.812 --> 01:05:40.212
And she was always there.

691
01:05:40.572 --> 01:05:42.212
Come with me. l'll show you.

692
01:05:51.211 --> 01:05:53.531
"Will we see him...

693
01:05:55.451 --> 01:05:57.211
come back?''

694
01:06:00.811 --> 01:06:03.210
This is Mr. and Mrs. Legendre,
Aliette's parents.


695
01:06:05.250 --> 01:06:08.890
When the children came into class,
the teacher counted them.


696
01:06:10.450 --> 01:06:12.650
There were 22 girls, as usual.

697
01:06:13.530 --> 01:06:17.409
Five minutes later,
she noticed Aliette wasn't there.


698
01:06:17.609 --> 01:06:18.969
She called me right away.

699
01:06:21.089 --> 01:06:23.489
- Could she have run away?
- lmpossible.


700
01:06:23.729 --> 01:06:26.529
The concierge was categorical:
No pupil left.


701
01:06:26.729 --> 01:06:29.088
lt's incredible.
lsn't anyone in charge?


702
01:06:29.648 --> 01:06:31.408
Sit down.

703
01:06:34.208 --> 01:06:35.968
l counted them too.

704
01:06:36.648 --> 01:06:39.528
l took the enrollment list
and called the roll.


705
01:06:40.448 --> 01:06:41.927
l've lost faith in this school.

706
01:06:42.127 --> 01:06:44.647
- Mommy.
- Be quiet. What do you want?


707
01:06:44.847 --> 01:06:46.327
l'm here.

708
01:06:47.007 --> 01:06:50.447
Be quiet when the headmistress
is talking. Understand?


709
01:06:50.807 --> 01:06:52.847
Now go back to your seat.

710
01:06:53.607 --> 01:06:55.966
l'll call the roll for you.
You'll see.


711
01:07:08.405 --> 01:07:09.685
Legendre, Aliette.

712
01:07:09.885 --> 01:07:11.245
Here.

713
01:07:14.165 --> 01:07:15.965
You see? She's there.

714
01:07:16.205 --> 01:07:17.525
And all the others are there?

715
01:07:17.725 --> 01:07:19.405
All of them. l checked.

716
01:07:19.605 --> 01:07:21.125
You looked everywhere?

717
01:07:21.325 --> 01:07:23.604
We searched the entire school.
Nothing.


718
01:07:23.844 --> 01:07:27.204
Good Lord!
What could have happened to her?


719
01:07:27.404 --> 01:07:32.124
lf you think we'll accept
your feeble explanation, you're wrong.


720
01:07:33.764 --> 01:07:35.963
We must notify the police at once.

721
01:07:41.323 --> 01:07:43.323
- Where's your coat?
- ln the hall.


722
01:08:03.161 --> 01:08:04.561
Show them in.

723
01:08:10.641 --> 01:08:12.161
Please come in.

724
01:08:14.680 --> 01:08:16.320
Do sit down.

725
01:08:20.600 --> 01:08:21.840
You are Mr. Legendre?

726
01:08:22.000 --> 01:08:24.480
Yes. Thanks for seeing us
so quickly.


727
01:08:24.680 --> 01:08:27.280
Not at all.
What can l do for you?


728
01:08:27.760 --> 01:08:30.559
- Our daughter has disappeared.
- When?


729
01:08:30.879 --> 01:08:33.919
About an hour ago,
when she got to school.


730
01:08:34.159 --> 01:08:35.719
The nanny took her as usual.

731
01:08:35.919 --> 01:08:38.999
When the teacher called the roll,
she was there.


732
01:08:39.199 --> 01:08:42.358
They searched the entire school,
but obviously they didn't find her.


733
01:08:43.438 --> 01:08:46.558
Do you have any enemies?
Anyone who would wish you harm?


734
01:08:47.598 --> 01:08:49.198
l don't think so.

735
01:08:49.998 --> 01:08:52.158
You're a man who's fairly -

736
01:08:53.118 --> 01:08:55.437
l mean, if it's a kidnapping,

737
01:08:55.597 --> 01:08:57.917
do you have the means
to pay a ransom?


738
01:08:58.837 --> 01:09:00.357
Yes, of course.

739
01:09:00.557 --> 01:09:02.877
l see. ls there a witness?

740
01:09:03.157 --> 01:09:04.277
The nanny.

741
01:09:04.477 --> 01:09:06.797
You took this child to school?

742
01:09:07.637 --> 01:09:12.796
Yes, sir. But l don't know a thing.
lt wasn't me.


743
01:09:13.036 --> 01:09:16.716
l left her at the gate,
like l always do. Didn't l, Aliette?


744
01:09:17.476 --> 01:09:19.596
That's right.
lt was like every day.


745
01:09:19.756 --> 01:09:21.595
She left me at the gate.

746
01:09:21.995 --> 01:09:24.235
You'll speak when you're questioned.

747
01:09:26.475 --> 01:09:29.795
First we'll fill out
a missing persons form.


748
01:09:30.995 --> 01:09:33.475
You did well to bring her.
lt helps.


749
01:09:33.675 --> 01:09:35.194
Come here, child.

750
01:09:40.674 --> 01:09:42.474
Now then...

751
01:09:43.354 --> 01:09:45.674
Legendre. Your first name?

752
01:09:47.873 --> 01:09:50.393
Race... white.

753
01:09:51.913 --> 01:09:54.433
- Age?
- Eight and a half.


754
01:09:55.113 --> 01:09:57.833
Marital status... single.

755
01:09:59.353 --> 01:10:01.712
Brown eyes.

756
01:10:02.472 --> 01:10:04.672
Auburn hair.

757
01:10:05.192 --> 01:10:06.832
Height?

758
01:10:07.992 --> 01:10:09.232
3'6''.

759
01:10:09.432 --> 01:10:10.792
Weight?

760
01:10:11.592 --> 01:10:12.872
Fifty-five pounds.

761
01:10:13.512 --> 01:10:15.951
Wearing a blue coat,
black shoes, white socks.


762
01:10:16.151 --> 01:10:18.711
Ask the sergeant to come in.

763
01:10:28.390 --> 01:10:31.830
lssue an all-points bulletin for Paris.
We must find this child.


764
01:10:33.830 --> 01:10:35.870
- This her?
- Yes, why?


765
01:10:36.070 --> 01:10:38.230
- Can't we take her along?
- No need.


766
01:10:38.430 --> 01:10:41.229
Just take a good look at her,
then get to work.


767
01:10:50.709 --> 01:10:54.508
Sergeant,
your shoes are far from spotless!


768
01:10:55.388 --> 01:10:57.788
You're right. l didn't have time to -

769
01:10:59.948 --> 01:11:03.708
So there's no need to worry.
We're pulling out all the stops.


770
01:11:03.908 --> 01:11:07.787
Contact us if you hear anything,
even if you're warned against it.


771
01:11:07.987 --> 01:11:08.747
Count on me.

772
01:11:08.947 --> 01:11:10.907
- Thank you, lnspector.
- Don't mention it.


773
01:11:46.385 --> 01:11:48.464
A fine-looking dog you have.

774
01:11:48.704 --> 01:11:52.704
You keep him tied up all day?
- l let him run free from time to time.


775
01:11:53.224 --> 01:11:54.544
With all this traffic?

776
01:11:54.744 --> 01:11:56.224
He's used to it.

777
01:11:57.864 --> 01:11:59.944
- What's his name?
- Chico.


778
01:12:01.503 --> 01:12:02.983
Good boy!

779
01:12:03.503 --> 01:12:07.383
The bastards who mistreat animals
should be drowned.


780
01:12:08.143 --> 01:12:10.743
That's what the Gospel says...
more or less.


781
01:14:02.014 --> 01:14:02.974
What's the matter?

782
01:16:03.885 --> 01:16:05.325
There he is!

783
01:16:06.525 --> 01:16:08.525
lt's him.

784
01:16:09.445 --> 01:16:11.885
The open window on the top floor.
l'll call in.


785
01:17:28.799 --> 01:17:30.199
Court is in session.

786
01:17:47.637 --> 01:17:48.917
The defendant will rise.

787
01:17:49.757 --> 01:17:50.957
All right, all right.

788
01:17:54.717 --> 01:17:57.077
Here are the judgments
on the charges


789
01:17:57.437 --> 01:17:59.916
and the verdict.

790
01:18:01.356 --> 01:18:05.556
On the charge of first-degree murder

791
01:18:05.756 --> 01:18:07.516
the jury replied guilty,

792
01:18:07.716 --> 01:18:10.196
by a majority
of at least eight votes.


793
01:18:12.356 --> 01:18:15.715
As to extenuating circumstances,
the jury found none,


794
01:18:16.355 --> 01:18:18.555
by a majority
of at least eight votes.


795
01:18:20.795 --> 01:18:22.395
Under Articles 295,

796
01:18:22.595 --> 01:18:25.315
296, 297, 302, and 304,

797
01:18:25.515 --> 01:18:28.554
and Article 12 of the Penal Code,
the court,


798
01:18:28.754 --> 01:18:31.074
having deliberated
in accordance with the law,


799
01:18:31.314 --> 01:18:33.914
sentences Bernard Levasseur

800
01:18:34.154 --> 01:18:35.394
to death.

801
01:18:39.193 --> 01:18:40.833
Court is adjourned.

802
01:19:44.149 --> 01:19:45.868
May l have your autograph?

803
01:19:50.628 --> 01:19:52.108
Me too.

804
01:19:54.268 --> 01:19:56.148
The trial of the killer poet

805
01:19:56.348 --> 01:19:58.268
lasted 1 4 months.

806
01:19:58.588 --> 01:20:01.667
Meanwhile, the search
for the little girl continued.


807
01:20:02.467 --> 01:20:03.747
Then, one day...

808
01:20:10.947 --> 01:20:13.026
Mr. Commissioner,
Mr. Legendre is here.


809
01:20:13.226 --> 01:20:14.426
Show him in.

810
01:20:20.346 --> 01:20:22.666
- Mr. Commissioner.
- Sit down.


811
01:20:27.745 --> 01:20:30.785
After all this time,
you may have started losing hope.


812
01:20:30.985 --> 01:20:32.985
l have good news at last.

813
01:20:33.185 --> 01:20:35.025
You did it!
l don't believe it.


814
01:20:36.585 --> 01:20:38.145
Bring her in.

815
01:20:47.064 --> 01:20:48.344
Sit down, madam.

816
01:20:51.464 --> 01:20:54.143
- l waited two hours for you.
- l couldn't help it.


817
01:20:54.343 --> 01:20:56.263
- Why didn't you phone?
- l couldn't.


818
01:20:56.983 --> 01:20:59.823
Commissioner,
l don't know how to thank you.


819
01:21:00.103 --> 01:21:01.623
Was she well treated?

820
01:21:01.823 --> 01:21:03.583
She had everything she needed,
didn't she?


821
01:21:03.783 --> 01:21:06.422
Everything. As usual.

822
01:21:06.622 --> 01:21:08.062
How did you find her?

823
01:21:08.702 --> 01:21:11.222
l have the written statement.
l'll read it.


824
01:21:12.022 --> 01:21:13.902
lt's a rather unusual story.

825
01:21:14.542 --> 01:21:17.422
"On the night of February 7,
the population of Lisieux


826
01:21:17.622 --> 01:21:20.621
was awakened
by a deafening explosion.


827
01:21:22.461 --> 01:21:26.221
When rescue workers arrived,
they were amazed to find -''


828
01:21:28.941 --> 01:21:30.581
1 :30 already?

829
01:21:30.741 --> 01:21:33.100
l'm sorry.
l have an urgent appointment.


830
01:21:33.300 --> 01:21:34.180
Go ahead.

831
01:21:34.380 --> 01:21:37.620
My secretary will read it to you.
Do you mind, Jacqueline?


832
01:21:38.260 --> 01:21:40.260
Good-bye and excuse me.

833
01:21:42.340 --> 01:21:43.820
Written statement:

834
01:21:44.300 --> 01:21:45.819
"On the night of February 7,

835
01:21:46.019 --> 01:21:50.019
the population of Lisieux was awakened
by a deafening explosion.


836
01:21:50.579 --> 01:21:53.939
When rescue workers arrived,
they were amazed to find...''


837
01:22:01.498 --> 01:22:02.938
Shall l wait, sir?

838
01:22:03.138 --> 01:22:04.858
No, you're dismissed. Thank you.

839
01:22:24.337 --> 01:22:25.496
What?

840
01:22:25.936 --> 01:22:27.416
They're not here yet?

841
01:22:29.136 --> 01:22:30.896
But the appointment was for 1 :30.

842
01:22:31.056 --> 01:22:34.016
Listen,
turn off that music, will you?


843
01:22:34.736 --> 01:22:38.735
You can't go into a bar or restaurant
without hearing canned music.


844
01:22:38.895 --> 01:22:40.975
Turn it off, will you?
- Yes, sir.


845
01:22:49.815 --> 01:22:51.295
The usual?

846
01:22:52.014 --> 01:22:53.294
Of course.

847
01:23:12.653 --> 01:23:15.973
- Will you sit at the bar?
- No, l'll sit over there.


848
01:23:16.413 --> 01:23:18.252
l'll have a glass of port.

849
01:23:45.530 --> 01:23:48.610
l'm sorry to disturb you, but -

850
01:23:49.410 --> 01:23:51.210
Don't be afraid.

851
01:23:51.410 --> 01:23:53.410
l'm the police commissioner.

852
01:23:53.610 --> 01:23:54.810
Pleased to meet you.

853
01:23:55.010 --> 01:23:57.410
May l sit with you for a minute?

854
01:23:57.810 --> 01:23:59.209
Please do.

855
01:24:01.729 --> 01:24:03.609
Your port, ma'am.

856
01:24:03.889 --> 01:24:07.369
Your drink is at your table, sir.
- Leave it there.


857
01:24:09.049 --> 01:24:11.528
You come here often?
- This is my first time.


858
01:24:12.168 --> 01:24:14.528
l was troubled
when l saw you come in.


859
01:24:14.728 --> 01:24:17.488
May l tell you why?
- lf you wish.


860
01:24:18.088 --> 01:24:21.248
Today is the fourth anniversary
of my sister's death.


861
01:24:22.088 --> 01:24:23.888
l loved her deeply.

862
01:24:24.687 --> 01:24:28.127
She looked exactly like you.
l thought you were her.


863
01:24:28.607 --> 01:24:32.807
Same face, same voice, same walk.
Her name was Marguerite.


864
01:24:33.927 --> 01:24:35.607
My name is Estelle.

865
01:24:37.007 --> 01:24:38.486
One summer afternoon...

866
01:24:38.886 --> 01:24:41.606
it was unbearably hot.

867
01:25:13.764 --> 01:25:15.044
You still here?

868
01:25:15.244 --> 01:25:18.403
Didn't you have an appointment?
- lt's too hot to go.


869
01:25:18.603 --> 01:25:22.043
Too hot!
You'll never amount to anything!


870
01:26:14.679 --> 01:26:16.959
l don't think l'll go to Toulouse.

871
01:26:17.159 --> 01:26:18.679
l'm going to tell Mother.

872
01:26:19.159 --> 01:26:21.239
She'll be furious, but you're right.

873
01:26:21.439 --> 01:26:23.958
These family dinners:
the aunts and cousins -


874
01:26:24.438 --> 01:26:25.758
what a bore!

875
01:26:26.358 --> 01:26:27.718
l know.

876
01:26:27.918 --> 01:26:30.718
What would l do in Toulouse
at 3:00 p.m.?


877
01:26:31.278 --> 01:26:32.638
Take a nap.

878
01:26:35.998 --> 01:26:39.197
Do me a favor.
Play the Brahms Rhapsody.


879
01:26:39.357 --> 01:26:40.557
lf you like.

880
01:27:12.115 --> 01:27:14.235
She never did go to Toulouse.

881
01:27:15.035 --> 01:27:17.554
She died a few days later.

882
01:27:18.714 --> 01:27:20.354
Do you play piano, too?

883
01:27:20.554 --> 01:27:21.794
A little.

884
01:27:21.994 --> 01:27:24.954
- You're not French?
- l was born in ltaly.


885
01:27:25.594 --> 01:27:27.354
- Cigarette?
- No, thank you.


886
01:27:27.514 --> 01:27:28.994
May l?

887
01:27:29.634 --> 01:27:31.633
What did your sister die of?

888
01:27:32.073 --> 01:27:34.033
The miserere colic.

889
01:27:34.233 --> 01:27:35.673
What is that?

890
01:27:35.873 --> 01:27:38.553
lt's horrible,
especially in the final stages.


891
01:27:38.753 --> 01:27:41.593
You end up vomiting excre-

892
01:27:41.753 --> 01:27:43.672
Excuse me.
- How awful.


893
01:27:43.832 --> 01:27:45.112
Horrible.

894
01:27:47.352 --> 01:27:49.112
l must be going,

895
01:27:49.272 --> 01:27:51.472
But it was extraordinary
meeting you like this.


896
01:27:51.712 --> 01:27:55.832
l'd like to see you again,
invite you to the Policemen's Ball.


897
01:27:56.032 --> 01:27:57.711
l'd love to go.

898
01:27:57.911 --> 01:28:00.031
A call for you, sir.

899
01:28:00.271 --> 01:28:03.151
- ls it Marcel saying he's late?
- l don't think so.


900
01:28:03.351 --> 01:28:05.191
No one else knows l'm here.

901
01:28:05.391 --> 01:28:07.471
Shall l say l haven't seen you?

902
01:28:07.671 --> 01:28:10.270
No. Ask who's calling.

903
01:28:11.950 --> 01:28:14.310
Can't have a moment's peace.

904
01:28:14.510 --> 01:28:16.670
Would you mind giving me
your name and address?


905
01:28:18.830 --> 01:28:21.310
lt's your sister, 
Marguerite, sir.

906
01:28:22.710 --> 01:28:25.309
- What?
- She says she must speak to you.


907
01:28:26.269 --> 01:28:28.229
Georges, tell her to go screw herself.

908
01:28:28.949 --> 01:28:30.749
With your permission, madam.

909
01:28:31.549 --> 01:28:35.429
This must be a sick joke.
My sister's been dead for four years.


910
01:28:36.269 --> 01:28:37.948
But, sir...

911
01:28:38.268 --> 01:28:39.508
she insists.

912
01:28:39.708 --> 01:28:41.588
She wants to see you
tonight in the family vault.


913
01:28:41.788 --> 01:28:44.748
She says the key's
in your right-hand desk drawer.


914
01:28:45.548 --> 01:28:47.068
Why, that's true.

915
01:28:47.868 --> 01:28:49.148
Ask her

916
01:28:49.348 --> 01:28:52.787
what l requested she play
one hot summer day


917
01:28:53.347 --> 01:28:54.947
when l went in her room.

918
01:28:55.747 --> 01:29:00.107
The commissioner wants to know what
he asked you to play one hot summer day


919
01:29:00.307 --> 01:29:02.187
when he went in your room.

920
01:29:05.466 --> 01:29:07.706
The Brahms Rhapsody, sir.

921
01:29:15.666 --> 01:29:16.825
Give me that.

922
01:29:20.145 --> 01:29:21.785
Yes, speaking.
Who are you?


923
01:29:24.185 --> 01:29:26.785
Learn the true mystery
of death tonight?


924
01:29:57.782 --> 01:29:59.982
- What do you want?
- l want to come in.


925
01:30:00.302 --> 01:30:01.582
lt's closed.

926
01:30:01.782 --> 01:30:05.142
l'm Mr. Richepin.
My family vault is here. Let me in.


927
01:30:05.422 --> 01:30:07.422
You need a special authorization.

928
01:30:08.822 --> 01:30:11.021
l'm the police commissioner.

929
01:30:16.461 --> 01:30:18.981
Go in, then.
Shall l go with you?


930
01:30:19.181 --> 01:30:21.021
No need. Stay here.

931
01:32:00.373 --> 01:32:01.733
That's him!

932
01:32:04.413 --> 01:32:07.013
- What are you doing? Let go!
- Take him away!


933
01:32:07.213 --> 01:32:09.492
Don't you know who l am?

934
01:32:10.372 --> 01:32:12.492
Hands off!
l'm the police commissioner!


935
01:32:12.692 --> 01:32:16.092
- Explain it at the station.
- Let go, l said.


936
01:32:16.292 --> 01:32:19.092
Stand at attention
and give me your badge numbers!


937
01:32:51.609 --> 01:32:53.369
- The commissioner.
- Send him in.


938
01:33:08.848 --> 01:33:10.008
Sit down.

939
01:33:12.848 --> 01:33:16.367
l've been treated
in a most shameful manner.


940
01:33:16.647 --> 01:33:18.767
l couldn't even call my home.

941
01:33:20.687 --> 01:33:23.967
You were found last night
at the cemetery,


942
01:33:24.167 --> 01:33:26.327
desecrating a crypt.

943
01:33:26.527 --> 01:33:30.246
When arrested, you claimed
you were the police commissioner.


944
01:33:31.206 --> 01:33:33.526
You know full well l am.

945
01:33:34.406 --> 01:33:37.046
l order you to return
my belongings at once.


946
01:33:38.166 --> 01:33:40.886
And take me to my office.
You'll hear about this!


947
01:33:41.086 --> 01:33:42.166
Of course.

948
01:33:42.365 --> 01:33:46.325
As we were saying,
desecration of a crypt.


949
01:33:46.645 --> 01:33:48.405
lt was my sister's casket.

950
01:33:48.605 --> 01:33:50.045
Your sister?

951
01:33:51.165 --> 01:33:52.645
l went to see my sister.

952
01:33:53.085 --> 01:33:54.405
She phoned me!

953
01:33:55.844 --> 01:33:57.884
Back to his cell.

954
01:34:05.604 --> 01:34:08.244
Get me the police commissioner.
lt's urgent.


955
01:34:11.483 --> 01:34:13.123
Hello, Mr. Commissioner?

956
01:34:13.563 --> 01:34:16.363
Sorry to disturb you.
This is lnspector Dupuis.


957
01:34:17.163 --> 01:34:21.443
We've arrested a fellow who claims
to be the police commissioner.


958
01:34:22.242 --> 01:34:24.802
Claims to be the police commissioner?
How odd.


959
01:34:25.242 --> 01:34:27.122
Does he look like me?

960
01:34:27.602 --> 01:34:28.442
ls he pleasant?

961
01:34:29.042 --> 01:34:30.682
Not at all.

962
01:34:31.322 --> 01:34:32.522
l see.

963
01:34:32.722 --> 01:34:34.482
Bring him here right away.

964
01:34:54.360 --> 01:34:56.760
The commissioner will see you now.

965
01:35:17.598 --> 01:35:18.998
There you are.

966
01:35:19.158 --> 01:35:21.158
Come in. How are you?

967
01:35:21.358 --> 01:35:22.798
- Fine, and you?
- Fine, thanks.


968
01:35:24.278 --> 01:35:26.278
That will be all, lnspector.
Thank you.


969
01:35:28.598 --> 01:35:30.157
Won't you sit there?

970
01:35:30.797 --> 01:35:32.117
l'm fine here.

971
01:35:32.837 --> 01:35:36.437
Very well.
You there, and me here.


972
01:35:40.277 --> 01:35:41.837
Two glasses of scotch.

973
01:35:42.956 --> 01:35:45.316
You've put on weight.
- So have you.


974
01:35:45.836 --> 01:35:49.276
- All those official dinners.
- Always eating and drinking.


975
01:35:49.476 --> 01:35:51.476
We ought to refuse.
- Not easy.


976
01:35:51.676 --> 01:35:53.556
What are you doing this morning?

977
01:35:54.196 --> 01:35:57.875
- This morning, you know -
- Ah, yes, the zoo. At noon.


978
01:35:58.555 --> 01:36:00.675
l've taken precautions.

979
01:36:00.875 --> 01:36:03.755
l've stationed

980
01:36:03.955 --> 01:36:05.235
But not grouped together.

981
01:36:05.395 --> 01:36:07.475
Spread them out:
some here, some there.


982
01:36:07.675 --> 01:36:09.194
We mustn't alarm people.

983
01:36:09.714 --> 01:36:13.434
The main thing is to keep them
from reaching the cages.


984
01:36:13.634 --> 01:36:16.674
The locks have been
carefully checked.


985
01:36:16.874 --> 01:36:20.474
And anyway, if some animals
are killed, tough luck.


986
01:36:21.274 --> 01:36:24.073
Our men are more valuable
than a zebra.


987
01:36:28.073 --> 01:36:29.953
To your health.

988
01:37:36.148 --> 01:37:37.868
Down with liberty!

989
01:37:39.548 --> 01:37:41.587
- Charge!
- And let 'em have it!